Title 
Understanding Website Analytics Using Google Analytics and WordPress 
Analytics 
Aim 
To understand the fundamentals of web analytics using Google Analytics and 
WordPress analytics tools, and to analyze website performance by preparing an 
analytical report based on traffic, user behavior, and content performance. 
Objectives 
1.
 
To understand the concept and importance of web analytics 
2.
 
To learn key metrics and dimensions used in Google Analytics 
3.
 
To understand the Google Analytics 4 (GA4) data model 
4.
 
To study basic analytics features available in WordPress 
5.
 
To analyze traffic and user behavior for a WordPress website 
6.
 
To prepare an analytical performance report with observations and 
improvement suggestions 





Theory 
Introduction to Web Analytics 
Web analytics is the process of collecting, measuring, analyzing, and interpreting 
website data to understand user behavior and improve website performance.
Web analytics helps answer questions such as: 
● 
How many users visit the website? 
● 
Where do users come from? 
● 
Which pages perform best? 
● 
How long do users stay on the site? 
● 
What actions do users take? 
Analytics enables data-driven decision making in digital marketing. 

Benefits of Google Analytics 
● 
Free and widely used 
● 
Detailed user behavior insights 
● 
Helps optimize content and SEO 
● 
Supports marketing performance measurement 
Limitations of Google Analytics 
● 
Learning curve for beginners 
● 
Data delay 
● 
Limited historical data retention in free version








Result 
